8489template <typename Derived>
8490OMPClause *
8491TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPScheduleClause(OMPScheduleClause *C) {
8492 ExprResult E = getDerived().TransformExpr(C->getChunkSize());
8493 if (E.isInvalid())
8494 return nullptr;
8495 return getDerived().RebuildOMPScheduleClause(
8496 C->getFirstScheduleModifier(), C->getSecondScheduleModifier(),
8497 C->getScheduleKind(), E.get(), C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(),
8498 C->getFirstScheduleModifierLoc(), C->getSecondScheduleModifierLoc(),
8499 C->getScheduleKindLoc(), C->getCommaLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
8500}

8513}

8682template <typename Derived>
8683OMPClause *
8684TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPReductionClause(OMPReductionClause *C) {
8685 llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
8686 Vars.reserve(C->varlist_size());
8687 for (auto *VE : C->varlists()) {
8688 ExprResult EVar = getDerived().TransformExpr(cast<Expr>(VE));
8689 if (EVar.isInvalid())
8690 return nullptr;
8691 Vars.push_back(EVar.get());
8692 }
8693 CXXScopeSpec ReductionIdScopeSpec;
8694 ReductionIdScopeSpec.Adopt(C->getQualifierLoc());
8695
8696 DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo = C->getNameInfo();
8697 if (NameInfo.getName()) {
8698 NameInfo = getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(NameInfo);
8699 if (!NameInfo.getName())
8700 return nullptr;
8701 }
8702 // Build a list of all UDR decls with the same names ranged by the Scopes.
8703 // The Scope boundary is a duplication of the previous decl.
8704 llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> UnresolvedReductions;
8705 for (auto *E : C->reduction_ops()) {
8706 // Transform all the decls.
8707 if (E) {
8708 auto *ULE = cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E);
8709 UnresolvedSet<8> Decls;
8710 for (auto *D : ULE->decls()) {
8711 NamedDecl *InstD =
8712 cast<NamedDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getExprLoc(), D));
8713 Decls.addDecl(InstD, InstD->getAccess());
8714 }
8715 UnresolvedReductions.push_back(
8716 UnresolvedLookupExpr::Create(
8717 SemaRef.Context, /*NamingClass=*/nullptr,
8718 ReductionIdScopeSpec.getWithLocInContext(SemaRef.Context),
8719 NameInfo, /*ADL=*/true, ULE->isOverloaded(),
8720 Decls.begin(), Decls.end()));
8721 } else
8722 UnresolvedReductions.push_back(nullptr);
8723 }
8724 return getDerived().RebuildOMPReductionClause(
8725 Vars, C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getColonLoc(),
8726 C->getEndLoc(), ReductionIdScopeSpec, NameInfo, UnresolvedReductions);
8727}
8728

8926
8927template <typename Derived, class T>
8928bool transformOMPMappableExprListClause(
8929 TreeTransform<Derived> &TT, OMPMappableExprListClause<T> *C,
8930 llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &Vars, CXXScopeSpec &MapperIdScopeSpec,
8931 DeclarationNameInfo &MapperIdInfo,
8932 llvm::SmallVectorImpl<Expr *> &UnresolvedMappers) {
8933 // Transform expressions in the list.
8934 Vars.reserve(C->varlist_size());
8935 for (auto *VE : C->varlists()) {
8936 ExprResult EVar = TT.getDerived().TransformExpr(cast<Expr>(VE));
8937 if (EVar.isInvalid())
8938 return true;
8939 Vars.push_back(EVar.get());
8940 }
8941 // Transform mapper scope specifier and identifier.
8942 NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
8943 if (C->getMapperQualifierLoc()) {
8944 QualifierLoc = TT.getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(
8945 C->getMapperQualifierLoc());
8946 if (!QualifierLoc)
8947 return true;
8948 }
8949 MapperIdScopeSpec.Adopt(QualifierLoc);
8950 MapperIdInfo = C->getMapperIdInfo();
8951 if (MapperIdInfo.getName()) {
8952 MapperIdInfo = TT.getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(MapperIdInfo);
8953 if (!MapperIdInfo.getName())
8954 return true;
8955 }
8956 // Build a list of all candidate OMPDeclareMapperDecls, which is provided by
8957 // the previous user-defined mapper lookup in dependent environment.
8958 for (auto *E : C->mapperlists()) {
8959 // Transform all the decls.
8960 if (E) {
8961 auto *ULE = cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(E);
8962 UnresolvedSet<8> Decls;
8963 for (auto *D : ULE->decls()) {
8964 NamedDecl *InstD =
8965 cast<NamedDecl>(TT.getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getExprLoc(), D));
8966 Decls.addDecl(InstD, InstD->getAccess());
8967 }
8968 UnresolvedMappers.push_back(UnresolvedLookupExpr::Create(
8969 TT.getSema().Context, /*NamingClass=*/nullptr,
8970 MapperIdScopeSpec.getWithLocInContext(TT.getSema().Context),
8971 MapperIdInfo, /*ADL=*/true, ULE->isOverloaded(), Decls.begin(),
8972 Decls.end()));
8973 } else {
8974 UnresolvedMappers.push_back(nullptr);
8975 }
8976 }
8977 return false;
8978}
8979
8980template <typename Derived>
8981OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPMapClause(OMPMapClause *C) {
8982 OMPVarListLocTy Locs(C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
8983 llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
8984 CXXScopeSpec MapperIdScopeSpec;
8985 DeclarationNameInfo MapperIdInfo;
8986 llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> UnresolvedMappers;
8987 if (transformOMPMappableExprListClause<Derived, OMPMapClause>(
8988 *this, C, Vars, MapperIdScopeSpec, MapperIdInfo, UnresolvedMappers))
8989 return nullptr;
8990 return getDerived().RebuildOMPMapClause(
8991 C->getMapTypeModifiers(), C->getMapTypeModifiersLoc(), MapperIdScopeSpec,
8992 MapperIdInfo, C->getMapType(), C->isImplicitMapType(), C->getMapLoc(),
8993 C->getColonLoc(), Vars, Locs, UnresolvedMappers);
8994}

8996template <typename Derived>
8997OMPClause *
8998TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPAllocateClause(OMPAllocateClause *C) {
8999 Expr *Allocator = C->getAllocator();
9000 if (Allocator) {
9001 ExprResult AllocatorRes = getDerived().TransformExpr(Allocator);
9002 if (AllocatorRes.isInvalid())
9003 return nullptr;
9004 Allocator = AllocatorRes.get();
9005 }
9006 llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
9007 Vars.reserve(C->varlist_size());
9008 for (auto *VE : C->varlists()) {
9009 ExprResult EVar = getDerived().TransformExpr(cast<Expr>(VE));
9010 if (EVar.isInvalid())
9011 return nullptr;
9012 Vars.push_back(EVar.get());
9013 }
9014 return getDerived().RebuildOMPAllocateClause(
9015 Allocator, Vars, C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getColonLoc(),
9016 C->getEndLoc());
9017}

9069template <typename Derived>
9070OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPHintClause(OMPHintClause *C) {
9071 ExprResult E = getDerived().TransformExpr(C->getHint());
9072 if (E.isInvalid())
9073 return nullptr;
9074 return getDerived().RebuildOMPHintClause(E.get(), C->getBeginLoc(),
9075 C->getLParenLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
9076}

9078template <typename Derived>
9079OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPDistScheduleClause(
9080 OMPDistScheduleClause *C) {
9081 ExprResult E = getDerived().TransformExpr(C->getChunkSize());
9082 if (E.isInvalid())
9083 return nullptr;
9084 return getDerived().RebuildOMPDistScheduleClause(
9085 C->getDistScheduleKind(), E.get(), C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(),
9086 C->getDistScheduleKindLoc(), C->getCommaLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
9087}

9095template <typename Derived>
9096OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPToClause(OMPToClause *C) {
9097 OMPVarListLocTy Locs(C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
9098 llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
9099 CXXScopeSpec MapperIdScopeSpec;
9100 DeclarationNameInfo MapperIdInfo;
9101 llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> UnresolvedMappers;
9102 if (transformOMPMappableExprListClause<Derived, OMPToClause>(
9103 *this, C, Vars, MapperIdScopeSpec, MapperIdInfo, UnresolvedMappers))
9104 return nullptr;
9105 return getDerived().RebuildOMPToClause(Vars, MapperIdScopeSpec, MapperIdInfo,
9106 Locs, UnresolvedMappers);
9107}

9109template <typename Derived>
9110OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPFromClause(OMPFromClause *C) {
9111 OMPVarListLocTy Locs(C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
9112 llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
9113 CXXScopeSpec MapperIdScopeSpec;
9114 DeclarationNameInfo MapperIdInfo;
9115 llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> UnresolvedMappers;
9116 if (transformOMPMappableExprListClause<Derived, OMPFromClause>(
9117 *this, C, Vars, MapperIdScopeSpec, MapperIdInfo, UnresolvedMappers))
9118 return nullptr;
9119 return getDerived().RebuildOMPFromClause(
9120 Vars, MapperIdScopeSpec, MapperIdInfo, Locs, UnresolvedMappers);
9121}

9123template <typename Derived>
9124OMPClause *TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPUseDevicePtrClause(
9125 OMPUseDevicePtrClause *C) {
9126 llvm::SmallVector<Expr *, 16> Vars;
9127 Vars.reserve(C->varlist_size());
9128 for (auto *VE : C->varlists()) {
9129 ExprResult EVar = getDerived().TransformExpr(cast<Expr>(VE));
9130 if (EVar.isInvalid())
9131 return nullptr;
9132 Vars.push_back(EVar.get());
9133 }
9134 OMPVarListLocTy Locs(C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
9135 return getDerived().RebuildOMPUseDevicePtrClause(Vars, Locs);
9136}

9146 return nullptr;
9147 Vars.push_back(EVar.get());

9149 OMPVarListLocTy Locs(C->getBeginLoc(), C->getLParenLoc(), C->getEndLoc());
9150 return getDerived().RebuildOMPIsDevicePtrClause(Vars, Locs);

9164TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformPredefinedExpr(PredefinedExpr *E) {
9165 if (!E->isTypeDependent())
9166 return E;

9172template<typename Derived>
9173ExprResult
9174TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDeclRefExpr(DeclRefExpr *E) {
9175 NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
9176 if (E->getQualifierLoc()) {
9177 QualifierLoc
9178 = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(E->getQualifierLoc());
9179 if (!QualifierLoc)
9180 return ExprError();
9181 }
9182
9183 ValueDecl *ND
9184 = cast_or_null<ValueDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getLocation(),
9185 E->getDecl()));
9186 if (!ND)
9187 return ExprError();
9188
9189 DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo = E->getNameInfo();
9190 if (NameInfo.getName()) {
9191 NameInfo = getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(NameInfo);
9192 if (!NameInfo.getName())
9193 return ExprError();
9194 }
9195
9196 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9197 QualifierLoc == E->getQualifierLoc() &&
9198 ND == E->getDecl() &&
9199 NameInfo.getName() == E->getDecl()->getDeclName() &&
9200 !E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
9201
9202 // Mark it referenced in the new context regardless.
9203 // FIXME: this is a bit instantiation-specific.
9204 SemaRef.MarkDeclRefReferenced(E);
9205
9206 return E;
9207 }
9208
9209 TemplateArgumentListInfo TransArgs, *TemplateArgs = nullptr;
9210 if (E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
9211 TemplateArgs = &TransArgs;
9212 TransArgs.setLAngleLoc(E->getLAngleLoc());
9213 TransArgs.setRAngleLoc(E->getRAngleLoc());
9214 if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(E->getTemplateArgs(),
9215 E->getNumTemplateArgs(),
9216 TransArgs))
9217 return ExprError();
9218 }
9219
9220 return getDerived().RebuildDeclRefExpr(QualifierLoc, ND, NameInfo,
9221 TemplateArgs);
9222}

9268template<typename Derived>
9269ExprResult
9270TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformGenericSelectionExpr(GenericSelectionExpr *E) {
9271 ExprResult ControllingExpr =
9272 getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getControllingExpr());
9273 if (ControllingExpr.isInvalid())
9274 return ExprError();
9275
9276 SmallVector<Expr *, 4> AssocExprs;
9277 SmallVector<TypeSourceInfo *, 4> AssocTypes;
9278 for (const GenericSelectionExpr::Association &Assoc : E->associations()) {
9279 TypeSourceInfo *TSI = Assoc.getTypeSourceInfo();
9280 if (TSI) {
9281 TypeSourceInfo *AssocType = getDerived().TransformType(TSI);
9282 if (!AssocType)
9283 return ExprError();
9284 AssocTypes.push_back(AssocType);
9285 } else {
9286 AssocTypes.push_back(nullptr);
9287 }
9288
9289 ExprResult AssocExpr =
9290 getDerived().TransformExpr(Assoc.getAssociationExpr());
9291 if (AssocExpr.isInvalid())
9292 return ExprError();
9293 AssocExprs.push_back(AssocExpr.get());
9294 }
9295
9296 return getDerived().RebuildGenericSelectionExpr(E->getGenericLoc(),
9297 E->getDefaultLoc(),
9298 E->getRParenLoc(),
9299 ControllingExpr.get(),
9300 AssocTypes,
9301 AssocExprs);
9302}

9304template<typename Derived>
9305ExprResult
9306TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformParenExpr(ParenExpr *E) {
9307 ExprResult SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSubExpr());
9308 if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
9309 return ExprError();
9310
9311 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && SubExpr.get() == E->getSubExpr())
9312 return E;
9313
9314 return getDerived().RebuildParenExpr(SubExpr.get(), E->getLParen(),
9315 E->getRParen());
9316}

9318/// The operand of a unary address-of operator has special rules: it's
9319/// allowed to refer to a non-static member of a class even if there's no 'this'
9320/// object available.
9321template<typename Derived>
9322ExprResult
9323TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformAddressOfOperand(Expr *E) {
9324 if (DependentScopeDeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DependentScopeDeclRefExpr>(E))
9325 return getDerived().TransformDependentScopeDeclRefExpr(DRE, true, nullptr);
9326 else
9327 return getDerived().TransformExpr(E);
9328}

9330template<typename Derived>
9331ExprResult
9332TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformUnaryOperator(UnaryOperator *E) {
9333 ExprResult SubExpr;
9334 if (E->getOpcode() == UO_AddrOf)
9335 SubExpr = TransformAddressOfOperand(E->getSubExpr());
9336 else
9337 SubExpr = TransformExpr(E->getSubExpr());
9338 if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
9339 return ExprError();
9340
9341 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && SubExpr.get() == E->getSubExpr())
9342 return E;
9343
9344 return getDerived().RebuildUnaryOperator(E->getOperatorLoc(),
9345 E->getOpcode(),
9346 SubExpr.get());
9347}
9348
9349template<typename Derived>
9350ExprResult
9351TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOffsetOfExpr(OffsetOfExpr *E) {
9352 // Transform the type.
9353 TypeSourceInfo *Type = getDerived().TransformType(E->getTypeSourceInfo());
9354 if (!Type)
9355 return ExprError();
9356
9357 // Transform all of the components into components similar to what the
9358 // parser uses.
9359 // FIXME: It would be slightly more efficient in the non-dependent case to
9360 // just map FieldDecls, rather than requiring the rebuilder to look for
9361 // the fields again. However, __builtin_offsetof is rare enough in
9362 // template code that we don't care.
9363 bool ExprChanged = false;
9364 typedef Sema::OffsetOfComponent Component;
9365 SmallVector<Component, 4> Components;
9366 for (unsigned I = 0, N = E->getNumComponents(); I != N; ++I) {
9367 const OffsetOfNode &ON = E->getComponent(I);
9368 Component Comp;
9369 Comp.isBrackets = true;
9370 Comp.LocStart = ON.getSourceRange().getBegin();
9371 Comp.LocEnd = ON.getSourceRange().getEnd();
9372 switch (ON.getKind()) {
9373 case OffsetOfNode::Array: {
9374 Expr *FromIndex = E->getIndexExpr(ON.getArrayExprIndex());
9375 ExprResult Index = getDerived().TransformExpr(FromIndex);
9376 if (Index.isInvalid())
9377 return ExprError();
9378
9379 ExprChanged = ExprChanged || Index.get() != FromIndex;
9380 Comp.isBrackets = true;
9381 Comp.U.E = Index.get();
9382 break;
9383 }
9384
9385 case OffsetOfNode::Field:
9386 case OffsetOfNode::Identifier:
9387 Comp.isBrackets = false;
9388 Comp.U.IdentInfo = ON.getFieldName();
9389 if (!Comp.U.IdentInfo)
9390 continue;
9391
9392 break;
9393
9394 case OffsetOfNode::Base:
9395 // Will be recomputed during the rebuild.
9396 continue;
9397 }
9398
9399 Components.push_back(Comp);
9400 }
9401
9402 // If nothing changed, retain the existing expression.
9403 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9404 Type == E->getTypeSourceInfo() &&
9405 !ExprChanged)
9406 return E;
9407
9408 // Build a new offsetof expression.
9409 return getDerived().RebuildOffsetOfExpr(E->getOperatorLoc(), Type,
9410 Components, E->getRParenLoc());
9411}

9414ExprResult
9415TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOpaqueValueExpr(OpaqueValueExpr *E) {
9416 assert((!E->getSourceExpr() || getDerived().AlreadyTransformed(E->getType())) &&
9417 "opaque value expression requires transformation");
9418 return E;
9419}

9424 return E;

9426
9427template<typename Derived>
9428ExprResult
9429TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformPseudoObjectExpr(PseudoObjectExpr *E) {
9430 // Rebuild the syntactic form. The original syntactic form has
9431 // opaque-value expressions in it, so strip those away and rebuild
9432 // the result. This is a really awful way of doing this, but the
9433 // better solution (rebuilding the semantic expressions and
9434 // rebinding OVEs as necessary) doesn't work; we'd need
9435 // TreeTransform to not strip away implicit conversions.
9436 Expr *newSyntacticForm = SemaRef.recreateSyntacticForm(E);
9437 ExprResult result = getDerived().TransformExpr(newSyntacticForm);
9438 if (result.isInvalid()) return ExprError();
9439
9440 // If that gives us a pseudo-object result back, the pseudo-object
9441 // expression must have been an lvalue-to-rvalue conversion which we
9442 // should reapply.
9443 if (result.get()->hasPlaceholderType(BuiltinType::PseudoObject))
9444 result = SemaRef.checkPseudoObjectRValue(result.get());
9445
9446 return result;
9447}
9448
9449template<typename Derived>
9450ExprResult
9451TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformUnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr(
9452 UnaryExprOrTypeTraitExpr *E) {
9453 if (E->isArgumentType()) {
9454 TypeSourceInfo *OldT = E->getArgumentTypeInfo();
9455
9456 TypeSourceInfo *NewT = getDerived().TransformType(OldT);
9457 if (!NewT)
9458 return ExprError();
9459
9460 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && OldT == NewT)
9461 return E;
9462
9463 return getDerived().RebuildUnaryExprOrTypeTrait(NewT, E->getOperatorLoc(),
9464 E->getKind(),
9465 E->getSourceRange());
9466 }
9467
9468 // C++0x [expr.sizeof]p1:
9469 // The operand is either an expression, which is an unevaluated operand
9470 // [...]
9471 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
9472 SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated,
9473 Sema::ReuseLambdaContextDecl);
9474
9475 // Try to recover if we have something like sizeof(T::X) where X is a type.
9476 // Notably, there must be *exactly* one set of parens if X is a type.
9477 TypeSourceInfo *RecoveryTSI = nullptr;
9478 ExprResult SubExpr;
9479 auto *PE = dyn_cast<ParenExpr>(E->getArgumentExpr());
9480 if (auto *DRE =
9481 PE ? dyn_cast<DependentScopeDeclRefExpr>(PE->getSubExpr()) : nullptr)
9482 SubExpr = getDerived().TransformParenDependentScopeDeclRefExpr(
9483 PE, DRE, false, &RecoveryTSI);
9484 else
9485 SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArgumentExpr());
9486
9487 if (RecoveryTSI) {
9488 return getDerived().RebuildUnaryExprOrTypeTrait(
9489 RecoveryTSI, E->getOperatorLoc(), E->getKind(), E->getSourceRange());
9490 } else if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
9491 return ExprError();
9492
9493 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && SubExpr.get() == E->getArgumentExpr())
9494 return E;
9495
9496 return getDerived().RebuildUnaryExprOrTypeTrait(SubExpr.get(),
9497 E->getOperatorLoc(),
9498 E->getKind(),
9499 E->getSourceRange());
9500}

9502template<typename Derived>
9503ExprResult
9504TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformArraySubscriptExpr(ArraySubscriptExpr *E) {
9505 ExprResult LHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLHS());
9506 if (LHS.isInvalid())
9507 return ExprError();
9508
9509 ExprResult RHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getRHS());
9510 if (RHS.isInvalid())
9511 return ExprError();
9512
9513
9514 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9515 LHS.get() == E->getLHS() &&
9516 RHS.get() == E->getRHS())
9517 return E;
9518
9519 return getDerived().RebuildArraySubscriptExpr(
9520 LHS.get(),
9521 /*FIXME:*/ E->getLHS()->getBeginLoc(), RHS.get(), E->getRBracketLoc());
9522}

9524template <typename Derived>
9525ExprResult
9526TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformOMPArraySectionExpr(OMPArraySectionExpr *E) {
9527 ExprResult Base = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getBase());
9528 if (Base.isInvalid())
9529 return ExprError();
9530
9531 ExprResult LowerBound;
9532 if (E->getLowerBound()) {
9533 LowerBound = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLowerBound());
9534 if (LowerBound.isInvalid())
9535 return ExprError();
9536 }
9537
9538 ExprResult Length;
9539 if (E->getLength()) {
9540 Length = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLength());
9541 if (Length.isInvalid())
9542 return ExprError();
9543 }
9544
9545 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && Base.get() == E->getBase() &&
9546 LowerBound.get() == E->getLowerBound() && Length.get() == E->getLength())
9547 return E;
9548
9549 return getDerived().RebuildOMPArraySectionExpr(
9550 Base.get(), E->getBase()->getEndLoc(), LowerBound.get(), E->getColonLoc(),
9551 Length.get(), E->getRBracketLoc());
9552}
9553
9554template<typename Derived>
9555ExprResult
9556TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCallExpr(CallExpr *E) {
9557 // Transform the callee.
9558 ExprResult Callee = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getCallee());
9559 if (Callee.isInvalid())
9560 return ExprError();
9561
9562 // Transform arguments.
9563 bool ArgChanged = false;
9564 SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Args;
9565 if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getArgs(), E->getNumArgs(), true, Args,
9566 &ArgChanged))
9567 return ExprError();
9568
9569 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9570 Callee.get() == E->getCallee() &&
9571 !ArgChanged)
9572 return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
9573
9574 // FIXME: Wrong source location information for the '('.
9575 SourceLocation FakeLParenLoc
9576 = ((Expr *)Callee.get())->getSourceRange().getBegin();
9577 return getDerived().RebuildCallExpr(Callee.get(), FakeLParenLoc,
9578 Args,
9579 E->getRParenLoc());
9580}
9581
9582template<typename Derived>
9583ExprResult
9584TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformMemberExpr(MemberExpr *E) {
9585 ExprResult Base = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getBase());
9586 if (Base.isInvalid())
9587 return ExprError();
9588
9589 NestedNameSpecifierLoc QualifierLoc;
9590 if (E->hasQualifier()) {
9591 QualifierLoc
9592 = getDerived().TransformNestedNameSpecifierLoc(E->getQualifierLoc());
9593
9594 if (!QualifierLoc)
9595 return ExprError();
9596 }
9597 SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc = E->getTemplateKeywordLoc();
9598
9599 ValueDecl *Member
9600 = cast_or_null<ValueDecl>(getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getMemberLoc(),
9601 E->getMemberDecl()));
9602 if (!Member)
9603 return ExprError();
9604
9605 NamedDecl *FoundDecl = E->getFoundDecl();
9606 if (FoundDecl == E->getMemberDecl()) {
9607 FoundDecl = Member;
9608 } else {
9609 FoundDecl = cast_or_null<NamedDecl>(
9610 getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getMemberLoc(), FoundDecl));
9611 if (!FoundDecl)
9612 return ExprError();
9613 }
9614
9615 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9616 Base.get() == E->getBase() &&
9617 QualifierLoc == E->getQualifierLoc() &&
9618 Member == E->getMemberDecl() &&
9619 FoundDecl == E->getFoundDecl() &&
9620 !E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
9621
9622 // Mark it referenced in the new context regardless.
9623 // FIXME: this is a bit instantiation-specific.
9624 SemaRef.MarkMemberReferenced(E);
9625
9626 return E;
9627 }
9628
9629 TemplateArgumentListInfo TransArgs;
9630 if (E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()) {
9631 TransArgs.setLAngleLoc(E->getLAngleLoc());
9632 TransArgs.setRAngleLoc(E->getRAngleLoc());
9633 if (getDerived().TransformTemplateArguments(E->getTemplateArgs(),
9634 E->getNumTemplateArgs(),
9635 TransArgs))
9636 return ExprError();
9637 }
9638
9639 // FIXME: Bogus source location for the operator
9640 SourceLocation FakeOperatorLoc =
9641 SemaRef.getLocForEndOfToken(E->getBase()->getSourceRange().getEnd());
9642
9643 // FIXME: to do this check properly, we will need to preserve the
9644 // first-qualifier-in-scope here, just in case we had a dependent
9645 // base (and therefore couldn't do the check) and a
9646 // nested-name-qualifier (and therefore could do the lookup).
9647 NamedDecl *FirstQualifierInScope = nullptr;
9648 DeclarationNameInfo MemberNameInfo = E->getMemberNameInfo();
9649 if (MemberNameInfo.getName()) {
9650 MemberNameInfo = getDerived().TransformDeclarationNameInfo(MemberNameInfo);
9651 if (!MemberNameInfo.getName())
9652 return ExprError();
9653 }
9654
9655 return getDerived().RebuildMemberExpr(Base.get(), FakeOperatorLoc,
9656 E->isArrow(),
9657 QualifierLoc,
9658 TemplateKWLoc,
9659 MemberNameInfo,
9660 Member,
9661 FoundDecl,
9662 (E->hasExplicitTemplateArgs()
9663 ? &TransArgs : nullptr),
9664 FirstQualifierInScope);
9665}
9666
9667template<typename Derived>
9668ExprResult
9669TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformBinaryOperator(BinaryOperator *E) {
9670 ExprResult LHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLHS());
9671 if (LHS.isInvalid())
9672 return ExprError();
9673
9674 ExprResult RHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getRHS());
9675 if (RHS.isInvalid())
9676 return ExprError();
9677
9678 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9679 LHS.get() == E->getLHS() &&
9680 RHS.get() == E->getRHS())
9681 return E;
9682
9683 Sema::FPContractStateRAII FPContractState(getSema());
9684 getSema().FPFeatures = E->getFPFeatures();
9685
9686 return getDerived().RebuildBinaryOperator(E->getOperatorLoc(), E->getOpcode(),
9687 LHS.get(), RHS.get());
9688}

9690template<typename Derived>
9691ExprResult
9692TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCompoundAssignOperator(
9693 CompoundAssignOperator *E) {
9694 return getDerived().TransformBinaryOperator(E);
9695}
9696
9697template<typename Derived>
9698ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::
9699TransformBinaryConditionalOperator(BinaryConditionalOperator *e) {
9700 // Just rebuild the common and RHS expressions and see whether we
9701 // get any changes.
9702
9703 ExprResult commonExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(e->getCommon());
9704 if (commonExpr.isInvalid())
9705 return ExprError();
9706
9707 ExprResult rhs = getDerived().TransformExpr(e->getFalseExpr());
9708 if (rhs.isInvalid())
9709 return ExprError();
9710
9711 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9712 commonExpr.get() == e->getCommon() &&
9713 rhs.get() == e->getFalseExpr())
9714 return e;
9715
9716 return getDerived().RebuildConditionalOperator(commonExpr.get(),
9717 e->getQuestionLoc(),
9718 nullptr,
9719 e->getColonLoc(),
9720 rhs.get());
9721}
9722
9723template<typename Derived>
9724ExprResult
9725TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformConditionalOperator(ConditionalOperator *E) {
9726 ExprResult Cond = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getCond());
9727 if (Cond.isInvalid())
9728 return ExprError();
9729
9730 ExprResult LHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLHS());
9731 if (LHS.isInvalid())
9732 return ExprError();
9733
9734 ExprResult RHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getRHS());
9735 if (RHS.isInvalid())
9736 return ExprError();
9737
9738 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9739 Cond.get() == E->getCond() &&
9740 LHS.get() == E->getLHS() &&
9741 RHS.get() == E->getRHS())
9742 return E;
9743
9744 return getDerived().RebuildConditionalOperator(Cond.get(),
9745 E->getQuestionLoc(),
9746 LHS.get(),
9747 E->getColonLoc(),
9748 RHS.get());
9749}
9750
9751template<typename Derived>
9752ExprResult
9753TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformImplicitCastExpr(ImplicitCastExpr *E) {
9754 // Implicit casts are eliminated during transformation, since they
9755 // will be recomputed by semantic analysis after transformation.
9756 return getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSubExprAsWritten());
9757}
9758
9759template<typename Derived>
9760ExprResult
9761TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCStyleCastExpr(CStyleCastExpr *E) {
9762 TypeSourceInfo *Type = getDerived().TransformType(E->getTypeInfoAsWritten());
9763 if (!Type)
9764 return ExprError();
9765
9766 ExprResult SubExpr
9767 = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSubExprAsWritten());
9768 if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
9769 return ExprError();
9770
9771 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9772 Type == E->getTypeInfoAsWritten() &&
9773 SubExpr.get() == E->getSubExpr())
9774 return E;
9775
9776 return getDerived().RebuildCStyleCastExpr(E->getLParenLoc(),
9777 Type,
9778 E->getRParenLoc(),
9779 SubExpr.get());
9780}
9781
9782template<typename Derived>
9783ExprResult
9784TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCompoundLiteralExpr(CompoundLiteralExpr *E) {
9785 TypeSourceInfo *OldT = E->getTypeSourceInfo();
9786 TypeSourceInfo *NewT = getDerived().TransformType(OldT);
9787 if (!NewT)
9788 return ExprError();
9789
9790 ExprResult Init = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getInitializer());
9791 if (Init.isInvalid())
9792 return ExprError();
9793
9794 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9795 OldT == NewT &&
9796 Init.get() == E->getInitializer())
9797 return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
9798
9799 // Note: the expression type doesn't necessarily match the
9800 // type-as-written, but that's okay, because it should always be
9801 // derivable from the initializer.
9802
9803 return getDerived().RebuildCompoundLiteralExpr(
9804 E->getLParenLoc(), NewT,
9805 /*FIXME:*/ E->getInitializer()->getEndLoc(), Init.get());
9806}
9807
9808template<typename Derived>
9809ExprResult
9810TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformExtVectorElementExpr(ExtVectorElementExpr *E) {
9811 ExprResult Base = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getBase());
9812 if (Base.isInvalid())
9813 return ExprError();
9814
9815 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9816 Base.get() == E->getBase())
9817 return E;
9818
9819 // FIXME: Bad source location
9820 SourceLocation FakeOperatorLoc =
9821 SemaRef.getLocForEndOfToken(E->getBase()->getEndLoc());
9822 return getDerived().RebuildExtVectorElementExpr(Base.get(), FakeOperatorLoc,
9823 E->getAccessorLoc(),
9824 E->getAccessor());
9825}
9826
9827template<typename Derived>
9828ExprResult
9829TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformInitListExpr(InitListExpr *E) {
9830 if (InitListExpr *Syntactic = E->getSyntacticForm())
9831 E = Syntactic;
9832
9833 bool InitChanged = false;
9834
9835 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Context(
9836 getSema(), EnterExpressionEvaluationContext::InitList);
9837
9838 SmallVector<Expr*, 4> Inits;
9839 if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getInits(), E->getNumInits(), false,
9840 Inits, &InitChanged))
9841 return ExprError();
9842
9843 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !InitChanged) {
9844 // FIXME: Attempt to reuse the existing syntactic form of the InitListExpr
9845 // in some cases. We can't reuse it in general, because the syntactic and
9846 // semantic forms are linked, and we can't know that semantic form will
9847 // match even if the syntactic form does.
9848 }
9849
9850 return getDerived().RebuildInitList(E->getLBraceLoc(), Inits,
9851 E->getRBraceLoc());
9852}
9853
9854template<typename Derived>
9855ExprResult
9856TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDesignatedInitExpr(DesignatedInitExpr *E) {
9857 Designation Desig;
9858
9859 // transform the initializer value
9860 ExprResult Init = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getInit());
9861 if (Init.isInvalid())
9862 return ExprError();
9863
9864 // transform the designators.
9865 SmallVector<Expr*, 4> ArrayExprs;
9866 bool ExprChanged = false;
9867 for (const DesignatedInitExpr::Designator &D : E->designators()) {
9868 if (D.isFieldDesignator()) {
9869 Desig.AddDesignator(Designator::getField(D.getFieldName(),
9870 D.getDotLoc(),
9871 D.getFieldLoc()));
9872 if (D.getField()) {
9873 FieldDecl *Field = cast_or_null<FieldDecl>(
9874 getDerived().TransformDecl(D.getFieldLoc(), D.getField()));
9875 if (Field != D.getField())
9876 // Rebuild the expression when the transformed FieldDecl is
9877 // different to the already assigned FieldDecl.
9878 ExprChanged = true;
9879 } else {
9880 // Ensure that the designator expression is rebuilt when there isn't
9881 // a resolved FieldDecl in the designator as we don't want to assign
9882 // a FieldDecl to a pattern designator that will be instantiated again.
9883 ExprChanged = true;
9884 }
9885 continue;
9886 }
9887
9888 if (D.isArrayDesignator()) {
9889 ExprResult Index = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArrayIndex(D));
9890 if (Index.isInvalid())
9891 return ExprError();
9892
9893 Desig.AddDesignator(
9894 Designator::getArray(Index.get(), D.getLBracketLoc()));
9895
9896 ExprChanged = ExprChanged || Init.get() != E->getArrayIndex(D);
9897 ArrayExprs.push_back(Index.get());
9898 continue;
9899 }
9900
9901 assert(D.isArrayRangeDesignator() && "New kind of designator?");
9902 ExprResult Start
9903 = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArrayRangeStart(D));
9904 if (Start.isInvalid())
9905 return ExprError();
9906
9907 ExprResult End = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArrayRangeEnd(D));
9908 if (End.isInvalid())
9909 return ExprError();
9910
9911 Desig.AddDesignator(Designator::getArrayRange(Start.get(),
9912 End.get(),
9913 D.getLBracketLoc(),
9914 D.getEllipsisLoc()));
9915
9916 ExprChanged = ExprChanged || Start.get() != E->getArrayRangeStart(D) ||
9917 End.get() != E->getArrayRangeEnd(D);
9918
9919 ArrayExprs.push_back(Start.get());
9920 ArrayExprs.push_back(End.get());
9921 }
9922
9923 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9924 Init.get() == E->getInit() &&
9925 !ExprChanged)
9926 return E;
9927
9928 return getDerived().RebuildDesignatedInitExpr(Desig, ArrayExprs,
9929 E->getEqualOrColonLoc(),
9930 E->usesGNUSyntax(), Init.get());
9931}

9933// Seems that if TransformInitListExpr() only works on the syntactic form of an
9934// InitListExpr, then a DesignatedInitUpdateExpr is not encountered.
9935template<typename Derived>
9936ExprResult
9937TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformDesignatedInitUpdateExpr(
9938 DesignatedInitUpdateExpr *E) {
9939 llvm_unreachable("Unexpected DesignatedInitUpdateExpr in syntactic form of "
9940 "initializer");
9941 return ExprError();
9942}

9966template<typename Derived>
9967ExprResult
9968TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformImplicitValueInitExpr(
9969 ImplicitValueInitExpr *E) {
9970 TemporaryBase Rebase(*this, E->getBeginLoc(), DeclarationName());
9971
9972 // FIXME: Will we ever have proper type location here? Will we actually
9973 // need to transform the type?
9974 QualType T = getDerived().TransformType(E->getType());
9975 if (T.isNull())
9976 return ExprError();
9977
9978 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9979 T == E->getType())
9980 return E;
9981
9982 return getDerived().RebuildImplicitValueInitExpr(T);

9985template<typename Derived>
9986ExprResult
9987TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformVAArgExpr(VAArgExpr *E) {
9988 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo = getDerived().TransformType(E->getWrittenTypeInfo());
9989 if (!TInfo)
9990 return ExprError();
9991
9992 ExprResult SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSubExpr());
9993 if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
9994 return ExprError();
9995
9996 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
9997 TInfo == E->getWrittenTypeInfo() &&
9998 SubExpr.get() == E->getSubExpr())
9999 return E;
10000
10001 return getDerived().RebuildVAArgExpr(E->getBuiltinLoc(), SubExpr.get(),
10002 TInfo, E->getRParenLoc());
10003}

10007TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformParenListExpr(ParenListExpr *E) {

10010 if (TransformExprs(E->getExprs(), E->getNumExprs(), true, Inits,
10011 &ArgumentChanged))
10012 return ExprError();
10013

10015 Inits,
10016 E->getRParenLoc());

10019/// Transform an address-of-label expression.
10020///
10021/// By default, the transformation of an address-of-label expression always
10022/// rebuilds the expression, so that the label identifier can be resolved to
10023/// the corresponding label statement by semantic analysis.
10024template<typename Derived>
10025ExprResult
10026TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformAddrLabelExpr(AddrLabelExpr *E) {
10027 Decl *LD = getDerived().TransformDecl(E->getLabel()->getLocation(),
10028 E->getLabel());
10029 if (!LD)
10030 return ExprError();
10031
10032 return getDerived().RebuildAddrLabelExpr(E->getAmpAmpLoc(), E->getLabelLoc(),
10033 cast<LabelDecl>(LD));
10034}

10036template<typename Derived>
10037ExprResult
10038TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformStmtExpr(StmtExpr *E) {
10039 SemaRef.ActOnStartStmtExpr();
10040 StmtResult SubStmt
10041 = getDerived().TransformCompoundStmt(E->getSubStmt(), true);
10042 if (SubStmt.isInvalid()) {
10043 SemaRef.ActOnStmtExprError();
10044 return ExprError();
10045 }
10046
10047 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
10048 SubStmt.get() == E->getSubStmt()) {
10049 // Calling this an 'error' is unintuitive, but it does the right thing.
10050 SemaRef.ActOnStmtExprError();
10051 return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
10052 }
10053
10054 return getDerived().RebuildStmtExpr(E->getLParenLoc(),
10055 SubStmt.get(),
10056 E->getRParenLoc());
10057}
10058
10059template<typename Derived>
10060ExprResult
10061TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformChooseExpr(ChooseExpr *E) {
10062 ExprResult Cond = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getCond());
10063 if (Cond.isInvalid())
10064 return ExprError();
10065
10066 ExprResult LHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getLHS());
10067 if (LHS.isInvalid())
10068 return ExprError();
10069
10070 ExprResult RHS = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getRHS());
10071 if (RHS.isInvalid())
10072 return ExprError();
10073
10074 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
10075 Cond.get() == E->getCond() &&
10076 LHS.get() == E->getLHS() &&
10077 RHS.get() == E->getRHS())
10078 return E;
10079
10080 return getDerived().RebuildChooseExpr(E->getBuiltinLoc(),
10081 Cond.get(), LHS.get(), RHS.get(),
10082 E->getRParenLoc());
10083}

10090
10091template<typename Derived>
10092ExprResult
10093TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXOperatorCallExpr(CXXOperatorCallExpr *E) {
10094 switch (E->getOperator()) {
10095 case OO_New:
10096 case OO_Delete:
10097 case OO_Array_New:
10098 case OO_Array_Delete:
10099 llvm_unreachable("new and delete operators cannot use CXXOperatorCallExpr");
10100
10101 case OO_Call: {
10102 // This is a call to an object's operator().
10103 assert(E->getNumArgs() >= 1 && "Object call is missing arguments");
10104
10105 // Transform the object itself.
10106 ExprResult Object = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArg(0));
10107 if (Object.isInvalid())
10108 return ExprError();
10109
10110 // FIXME: Poor location information
10111 SourceLocation FakeLParenLoc = SemaRef.getLocForEndOfToken(
10112 static_cast<Expr *>(Object.get())->getEndLoc());
10113
10114 // Transform the call arguments.
10115 SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Args;
10116 if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getArgs() + 1, E->getNumArgs() - 1, true,
10117 Args))
10118 return ExprError();
10119
10120 return getDerived().RebuildCallExpr(Object.get(), FakeLParenLoc, Args,
10121 E->getEndLoc());
10122 }
10123
10124#define OVERLOADED_OPERATOR(Name,Spelling,Token,Unary,Binary,MemberOnly) \
10125 case OO_##Name:
10126#define OVERLOADED_OPERATOR_MULTI(Name,Spelling,Unary,Binary,MemberOnly)
10127#include "clang/Basic/OperatorKinds.def"
10128 case OO_Subscript:
10129 // Handled below.
10130 break;
10131
10132 case OO_Conditional:
10133 llvm_unreachable("conditional operator is not actually overloadable");
10134
10135 case OO_None:
10136 case NUM_OVERLOADED_OPERATORS:
10137 llvm_unreachable("not an overloaded operator?");
10138 }
10139
10140 ExprResult Callee = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getCallee());
10141 if (Callee.isInvalid())
10142 return ExprError();
10143
10144 ExprResult First;
10145 if (E->getOperator() == OO_Amp)
10146 First = getDerived().TransformAddressOfOperand(E->getArg(0));
10147 else
10148 First = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArg(0));
10149 if (First.isInvalid())
10150 return ExprError();
10151
10152 ExprResult Second;
10153 if (E->getNumArgs() == 2) {
10154 Second = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getArg(1));
10155 if (Second.isInvalid())
10156 return ExprError();
10157 }
10158
10159 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
10160 Callee.get() == E->getCallee() &&
10161 First.get() == E->getArg(0) &&
10162 (E->getNumArgs() != 2 || Second.get() == E->getArg(1)))
10163 return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
10164
10165 Sema::FPContractStateRAII FPContractState(getSema());
10166 getSema().FPFeatures = E->getFPFeatures();
10167
10168 return getDerived().RebuildCXXOperatorCallExpr(E->getOperator(),
10169 E->getOperatorLoc(),
10170 Callee.get(),
10171 First.get(),
10172 Second.get());
10173}
10174
10175template<typename Derived>
10176ExprResult
10177TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXMemberCallExpr(CXXMemberCallExpr *E) {
10178 return getDerived().TransformCallExpr(E);
10179}
10180
10181template <typename Derived>
10182ExprResult TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformSourceLocExpr(SourceLocExpr *E) {
10183 bool NeedRebuildFunc = E->getIdentKind() == SourceLocExpr::Function &&
10184 getSema().CurContext != E->getParentContext();
10185
10186 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && !NeedRebuildFunc)
10187 return E;
10188
10189 return getDerived().RebuildSourceLocExpr(E->getIdentKind(), E->getBeginLoc(),
10190 E->getEndLoc(),
10191 getSema().CurContext);
10192}
10193
10194template<typename Derived>
10195ExprResult
10196TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCUDAKernelCallExpr(CUDAKernelCallExpr *E) {
10197 // Transform the callee.
10198 ExprResult Callee = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getCallee());
10199 if (Callee.isInvalid())
10200 return ExprError();
10201
10202 // Transform exec config.
10203 ExprResult EC = getDerived().TransformCallExpr(E->getConfig());
10204 if (EC.isInvalid())
10205 return ExprError();
10206
10207 // Transform arguments.
10208 bool ArgChanged = false;
10209 SmallVector<Expr*, 8> Args;
10210 if (getDerived().TransformExprs(E->getArgs(), E->getNumArgs(), true, Args,
10211 &ArgChanged))
10212 return ExprError();
10213
10214 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
10215 Callee.get() == E->getCallee() &&
10216 !ArgChanged)
10217 return SemaRef.MaybeBindToTemporary(E);
10218
10219 // FIXME: Wrong source location information for the '('.
10220 SourceLocation FakeLParenLoc
10221 = ((Expr *)Callee.get())->getSourceRange().getBegin();
10222 return getDerived().RebuildCallExpr(Callee.get(), FakeLParenLoc,
10223 Args,
10224 E->getRParenLoc(), EC.get());
10225}

10227template<typename Derived>
10228ExprResult
10229TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXNamedCastExpr(CXXNamedCastExpr *E) {
10230 TypeSourceInfo *Type = getDerived().TransformType(E->getTypeInfoAsWritten());
10231 if (!Type)
10232 return ExprError();
10233
10234 ExprResult SubExpr
10235 = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSubExprAsWritten());
10236 if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
10237 return ExprError();
10238
10239 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
10240 Type == E->getTypeInfoAsWritten() &&
10241 SubExpr.get() == E->getSubExpr())
10242 return E;
10243 return getDerived().RebuildCXXNamedCastExpr(
10244 E->getOperatorLoc(), E->getStmtClass(), E->getAngleBrackets().getBegin(),
10245 Type, E->getAngleBrackets().getEnd(),
10246 // FIXME. this should be '(' location
10247 E->getAngleBrackets().getEnd(), SubExpr.get(), E->getRParenLoc());
10248}

10275template<typename Derived>

10277TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXFunctionalCastExpr(
10278 CXXFunctionalCastExpr *E) {

10280 getDerived().TransformTypeWithDeducedTST(E->getTypeInfoAsWritten());
10281 if (!Type)
10282 return ExprError();
10283

10285 = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getSubExprAsWritten());
10286 if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
10287 return ExprError();

10290 Type == E->getTypeInfoAsWritten() &&

10301template<typename Derived>
10302ExprResult
10303TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXTypeidExpr(CXXTypeidExpr *E) {
10304 if (E->isTypeOperand()) {
10305 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo
10306 = getDerived().TransformType(E->getTypeOperandSourceInfo());
10307 if (!TInfo)
10308 return ExprError();
10309
10310 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
10311 TInfo == E->getTypeOperandSourceInfo())
10312 return E;
10313
10314 return getDerived().RebuildCXXTypeidExpr(E->getType(), E->getBeginLoc(),
10315 TInfo, E->getEndLoc());
10316 }
10317
10318 // We don't know whether the subexpression is potentially evaluated until
10319 // after we perform semantic analysis. We speculatively assume it is
10320 // unevaluated; it will get fixed later if the subexpression is in fact
10321 // potentially evaluated.
10322 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
10323 SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated,
10324 Sema::ReuseLambdaContextDecl);
10325
10326 ExprResult SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getExprOperand());
10327 if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
10328 return ExprError();
10329
10330 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
10331 SubExpr.get() == E->getExprOperand())
10332 return E;
10333
10334 return getDerived().RebuildCXXTypeidExpr(E->getType(), E->getBeginLoc(),
10335 SubExpr.get(), E->getEndLoc());
10336}

10338template<typename Derived>
10339ExprResult
10340TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXUuidofExpr(CXXUuidofExpr *E) {
10341 if (E->isTypeOperand()) {
10342 TypeSourceInfo *TInfo
10343 = getDerived().TransformType(E->getTypeOperandSourceInfo());
10344 if (!TInfo)
10345 return ExprError();
10346
10347 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
10348 TInfo == E->getTypeOperandSourceInfo())
10349 return E;
10350
10351 return getDerived().RebuildCXXUuidofExpr(E->getType(), E->getBeginLoc(),
10352 TInfo, E->getEndLoc());
10353 }
10354
10355 EnterExpressionEvaluationContext Unevaluated(
10356 SemaRef, Sema::ExpressionEvaluationContext::Unevaluated);
10357
10358 ExprResult SubExpr = getDerived().TransformExpr(E->getExprOperand());
10359 if (SubExpr.isInvalid())
10360 return ExprError();
10361
10362 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() &&
10363 SubExpr.get() == E->getExprOperand())
10364 return E;
10365
10366 return getDerived().RebuildCXXUuidofExpr(E->getType(), E->getBeginLoc(),
10367 SubExpr.get(), E->getEndLoc());
10368}

10383template<typename Derived>
10384ExprResult
10385TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCXXThisExpr(CXXThisExpr *E) {
10386 QualType T = getSema().getCurrentThisType();
10387
10388 if (!getDerived().AlwaysRebuild() && T == E->getType()) {
10389 // Mark it referenced in the new context regardless.
10390 // FIXME: this is a bit instantiation-specific.
10391 getSema().MarkThisReferenced(E);
10392 return E;
10393 }
10394
10395 return getDerived().RebuildCXXThisExpr(E->getBeginLoc(), T, E->isImplicit());
10396}
