12864
12865template<typename Derived>
12866QualType TreeTransform<Derived>::RebuildUnresolvedUsingType(SourceLocation Loc,
12867 Decl *D) {
12868 assert(D && "no decl found");
12869 if (D->isInvalidDecl()) return QualType();
12870
12871 // FIXME: Doesn't account for ObjCInterfaceDecl!
12872 TypeDecl *Ty;
12873 if (auto *UPD = dyn_cast<UsingPackDecl>(D)) {
12874 // A valid resolved using typename pack expansion decl can have multiple
12875 // UsingDecls, but they must each have exactly one type, and it must be
12876 // the same type in every case. But we must have at least one expansion!
12877 if (UPD->expansions().empty()) {
12878 getSema().Diag(Loc, diag::err_using_pack_expansion_empty)
12879 << UPD->isCXXClassMember() << UPD;
12880 return QualType();
12881 }
12882
12883 // We might still have some unresolved types. Try to pick a resolved type
12884 // if we can. The final instantiation will check that the remaining
12885 // unresolved types instantiate to the type we pick.
12886 QualType FallbackT;
12887 QualType T;
12888 for (auto *E : UPD->expansions()) {
12889 QualType ThisT = RebuildUnresolvedUsingType(Loc, E);
12890 if (ThisT.isNull())
12891 continue;
12892 else if (ThisT->getAs<UnresolvedUsingType>())
12893 FallbackT = ThisT;
12894 else if (T.isNull())
12895 T = ThisT;
12896 else
12897 assert(getSema().Context.hasSameType(ThisT, T) &&
12898 "mismatched resolved types in using pack expansion");
12899 }
12900 return T.isNull() ? FallbackT : T;
12901 } else if (auto *Using = dyn_cast<UsingDecl>(D)) {
12902 assert(Using->hasTypename() &&
12903 "UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl transformed to non-typename using");
12904
12905 // A valid resolved using typename decl points to exactly one type decl.
12906 assert(++Using->shadow_begin() == Using->shadow_end());
12907 Ty = cast<TypeDecl>((*Using->shadow_begin())->getTargetDecl());
12908 } else {
12909 assert(isa<UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl>(D) &&
12910 "UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl transformed to non-using decl");
12911 Ty = cast<UnresolvedUsingTypenameDecl>(D);
12912 }
12913
12914 return SemaRef.Context.getTypeDeclType(Ty);
12915}

12973TemplateName
12974TreeTransform<Derived>::RebuildTemplateName(CXXScopeSpec &SS,

12992template<typename Derived>
12993TemplateName
12994TreeTransform<Derived>::RebuildTemplateName(CXXScopeSpec &SS,
12995 SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc,
12996 OverloadedOperatorKind Operator,
12997 SourceLocation NameLoc,
12998 QualType ObjectType,
12999 bool AllowInjectedClassName) {
13000 UnqualifiedId Name;
13001 // FIXME: Bogus location information.
13002 SourceLocation SymbolLocations[3] = { NameLoc, NameLoc, NameLoc };
13003 Name.setOperatorFunctionId(NameLoc, Operator, SymbolLocations);
13004 Sema::TemplateTy Template;
13005 getSema().ActOnDependentTemplateName(/*Scope=*/nullptr,
13006 SS, TemplateKWLoc, Name,
13007 ParsedType::make(ObjectType),
13008 /*EnteringContext=*/false,
13009 Template, AllowInjectedClassName);
13010 return Template.get();
13011}
13012
13013template<typename Derived>
13014ExprResult
13015TreeTransform<Derived>::RebuildCXXOperatorCallExpr(OverloadedOperatorKind Op,
13016 SourceLocation OpLoc,
13017 Expr *OrigCallee,
13018 Expr *First,
13019 Expr *Second) {
13020 Expr *Callee = OrigCallee->IgnoreParenCasts();
13021 bool isPostIncDec = Second && (Op == OO_PlusPlus || Op == OO_MinusMinus);
13022
13023 if (First->getObjectKind() == OK_ObjCProperty) {
13024 BinaryOperatorKind Opc = BinaryOperator::getOverloadedOpcode(Op);
13025 if (BinaryOperator::isAssignmentOp(Opc))
13026 return SemaRef.checkPseudoObjectAssignment(/*Scope=*/nullptr, OpLoc, Opc,
13027 First, Second);
13028 ExprResult Result = SemaRef.CheckPlaceholderExpr(First);
13029 if (Result.isInvalid())
13030 return ExprError();
13031 First = Result.get();
13032 }
13033
13034 if (Second && Second->getObjectKind() == OK_ObjCProperty) {
13035 ExprResult Result = SemaRef.CheckPlaceholderExpr(Second);
13036 if (Result.isInvalid())
13037 return ExprError();
13038 Second = Result.get();
13039 }
13040
13041 // Determine whether this should be a builtin operation.
13042 if (Op == OO_Subscript) {
13043 if (!First->getType()->isOverloadableType() &&
13044 !Second->getType()->isOverloadableType())
13045 return getSema().CreateBuiltinArraySubscriptExpr(
13046 First, Callee->getBeginLoc(), Second, OpLoc);
13047 } else if (Op == OO_Arrow) {
13048 // -> is never a builtin operation.
13049 return SemaRef.BuildOverloadedArrowExpr(nullptr, First, OpLoc);
13050 } else if (Second == nullptr || isPostIncDec) {
13051 if (!First->getType()->isOverloadableType() ||
13052 (Op == OO_Amp && getSema().isQualifiedMemberAccess(First))) {
13053 // The argument is not of overloadable type, or this is an expression
13054 // of the form &Class::member, so try to create a built-in unary
13055 // operation.
13056 UnaryOperatorKind Opc
13057 = UnaryOperator::getOverloadedOpcode(Op, isPostIncDec);
13058
13059 return getSema().CreateBuiltinUnaryOp(OpLoc, Opc, First);
13060 }
13061 } else {
13062 if (!First->getType()->isOverloadableType() &&
13063 !Second->getType()->isOverloadableType()) {
13064 // Neither of the arguments is an overloadable type, so try to
13065 // create a built-in binary operation.
13066 BinaryOperatorKind Opc = BinaryOperator::getOverloadedOpcode(Op);
13067 ExprResult Result
13068 = SemaRef.CreateBuiltinBinOp(OpLoc, Opc, First, Second);
13069 if (Result.isInvalid())
13070 return ExprError();
13071
13072 return Result;
13073 }
13074 }
13075
13076 // Compute the transformed set of functions (and function templates) to be
13077 // used during overload resolution.
13078 UnresolvedSet<16> Functions;
13079 bool RequiresADL;
13080
13081 if (UnresolvedLookupExpr *ULE = dyn_cast<UnresolvedLookupExpr>(Callee)) {
13082 Functions.append(ULE->decls_begin(), ULE->decls_end());
13083 // If the overload could not be resolved in the template definition
13084 // (because we had a dependent argument), ADL is performed as part of
13085 // template instantiation.
13086 RequiresADL = ULE->requiresADL();
13087 } else {
13088 // If we've resolved this to a particular non-member function, just call
13089 // that function. If we resolved it to a member function,
13090 // CreateOverloaded* will find that function for us.
13091 NamedDecl *ND = cast<DeclRefExpr>(Callee)->getDecl();
13092 if (!isa<CXXMethodDecl>(ND))
13093 Functions.addDecl(ND);
13094 RequiresADL = false;
13095 }
13096
13097 // Add any functions found via argument-dependent lookup.
13098 Expr *Args[2] = { First, Second };
13099 unsigned NumArgs = 1 + (Second != nullptr);
13100
13101 // Create the overloaded operator invocation for unary operators.
13102 if (NumArgs == 1 || isPostIncDec) {
13103 UnaryOperatorKind Opc
13104 = UnaryOperator::getOverloadedOpcode(Op, isPostIncDec);
13105 return SemaRef.CreateOverloadedUnaryOp(OpLoc, Opc, Functions, First,
13106 RequiresADL);
13107 }
13108
13109 if (Op == OO_Subscript) {
13110 SourceLocation LBrace;
13111 SourceLocation RBrace;
13112
13113 if (DeclRefExpr *DRE = dyn_cast<DeclRefExpr>(Callee)) {
13114 DeclarationNameLoc NameLoc = DRE->getNameInfo().getInfo();
13115 LBrace = SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(
13116 NameLoc.CXXOperatorName.BeginOpNameLoc);
13117 RBrace = SourceLocation::getFromRawEncoding(
13118 NameLoc.CXXOperatorName.EndOpNameLoc);
13119 } else {
13120 LBrace = Callee->getBeginLoc();
13121 RBrace = OpLoc;
13122 }
13123
13124 return SemaRef.CreateOverloadedArraySubscriptExpr(LBrace, RBrace,
13125 First, Second);
13126 }
13127
13128 // Create the overloaded operator invocation for binary operators.
13129 BinaryOperatorKind Opc = BinaryOperator::getOverloadedOpcode(Op);
13130 ExprResult Result = SemaRef.CreateOverloadedBinOp(
13131 OpLoc, Opc, Functions, Args[0], Args[1], RequiresADL);
13132 if (Result.isInvalid())
13133 return ExprError();
13134
13135 return Result;
13136}
13137
13138template<typename Derived>
13139ExprResult
13140TreeTransform<Derived>::RebuildCXXPseudoDestructorExpr(Expr *Base,
13141 SourceLocation OperatorLoc,
13142 bool isArrow,
13143 CXXScopeSpec &SS,
13144 TypeSourceInfo *ScopeType,
13145 SourceLocation CCLoc,
13146 SourceLocation TildeLoc,
13147 PseudoDestructorTypeStorage Destroyed) {
13148 QualType BaseType = Base->getType();
13149 if (Base->isTypeDependent() || Destroyed.getIdentifier() ||
13150 (!isArrow && !BaseType->getAs<RecordType>()) ||
13151 (isArrow && BaseType->getAs<PointerType>() &&
13152 !BaseType->getAs<PointerType>()->getPointeeType()
13153 ->template getAs<RecordType>())){
13154 // This pseudo-destructor expression is still a pseudo-destructor.
13155 return SemaRef.BuildPseudoDestructorExpr(
13156 Base, OperatorLoc, isArrow ? tok::arrow : tok::period, SS, ScopeType,
13157 CCLoc, TildeLoc, Destroyed);
13158 }
13159
13160 TypeSourceInfo *DestroyedType = Destroyed.getTypeSourceInfo();
13161 DeclarationName Name(SemaRef.Context.DeclarationNames.getCXXDestructorName(
13162 SemaRef.Context.getCanonicalType(DestroyedType->getType())));
13163 DeclarationNameInfo NameInfo(Name, Destroyed.getLocation());
13164 NameInfo.setNamedTypeInfo(DestroyedType);
13165
13166 // The scope type is now known to be a valid nested name specifier
13167 // component. Tack it on to the end of the nested name specifier.
13168 if (ScopeType) {
13169 if (!ScopeType->getType()->getAs<TagType>()) {
13170 getSema().Diag(ScopeType->getTypeLoc().getBeginLoc(),
13171 diag::err_expected_class_or_namespace)
13172 << ScopeType->getType() << getSema().getLangOpts().CPlusPlus;
13173 return ExprError();
13174 }
13175 SS.Extend(SemaRef.Context, SourceLocation(), ScopeType->getTypeLoc(),
13176 CCLoc);
13177 }
13178
13179 SourceLocation TemplateKWLoc; // FIXME: retrieve it from caller.
13180 return getSema().BuildMemberReferenceExpr(Base, BaseType,
13181 OperatorLoc, isArrow,
13182 SS, TemplateKWLoc,
13183 /*FIXME: FirstQualifier*/ nullptr,
13184 NameInfo,
13185 /*TemplateArgs*/ nullptr,
13186 /*S*/nullptr);
13187}
13188
13189template<typename Derived>
13190StmtResult
13191TreeTransform<Derived>::TransformCapturedStmt(CapturedStmt *S) {
13192 SourceLocation Loc = S->getBeginLoc();
13193 CapturedDecl *CD = S->getCapturedDecl();
13194 unsigned NumParams = CD->getNumParams();
13195 unsigned ContextParamPos = CD->getContextParamPosition();
13196 SmallVector<Sema::CapturedParamNameType, 4> Params;
13197 for (unsigned I = 0; I < NumParams; ++I) {
13198 if (I != ContextParamPos) {
13199 Params.push_back(
13200 std::make_pair(
13201 CD->getParam(I)->getName(),
13202 getDerived().TransformType(CD->getParam(I)->getType())));
13203 } else {
13204 Params.push_back(std::make_pair(StringRef(), QualType()));
13205 }
13206 }
13207 getSema().ActOnCapturedRegionStart(Loc, /*CurScope*/nullptr,
13208 S->getCapturedRegionKind(), Params);
13209 StmtResult Body;
13210 {
13211 Sema::CompoundScopeRAII CompoundScope(getSema());
13212 Body = getDerived().TransformStmt(S->getCapturedStmt());
13213 }
13214
13215 if (Body.isInvalid()) {
13216 getSema().ActOnCapturedRegionError();
13217 return StmtError();
13218 }
13219
13220 return getSema().ActOnCapturedRegionEnd(Body.get());
13221}
